Pātra  (IE 8-3;<BR>EI 28, 29;<BR>BL), a minister;<BR>cf. Mahāpurohita-ṭhakkura, Paṇḍita, Upādhyāya, Karaṇa-kāyastha, etc., mentioned as Pātra probably meaning ‘a courtier.’ See Ekapātra and Mahāpātra.

