vṛtti  (SITI), means;<BR>livelihood, occupation;<BR>grant of land for one's livelihood. (SII 3), land granted for service. (EI 17, 31;<BR>CITD), share;<BR>share in a village granted to a Brāhmaṇa as a free gift.

वु
Vu d8hā-leṅkā (EI 28), Od8iyā;<BR>official designation;<BR>cf. Leṅkā.

