yathākāl-ādhyāsin  (EI 4, 23), ‘one who may be employed [in the area including the gift land]<BR>from time to time’;<BR>one who may be associated with the area about the gift land in different periods of time;<BR>same as yathākāla-bhāvin, vartamāna-bhaviṣyat, yathā-sambadhyamānaka.

