yoga  (CII 4), meditation;<BR>a philosophical system.  (EI 18), a council or corporation. (CII 3;<BR>IA 17), addition of the longitudes of the sun and moon;<BR>an astrological element. Cf. yogaṁ yuñjantām, ‘let them obtain the association [of the gods]’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 208. Cf. yuj.

योगक्षेम
yoga-kṣema  (IA 7;<BR>LP), death;<BR>cf. jāta-yoga-kṣema, dead.

