युगा
yugā  (CII 4), a voucher.

युगादि
yug-ādi  (CII 4;<BR>IA 18), name applied to certain tithis; day of the commencement of a yuga; e. g. Vaiśākha-sudi 3, regarded as the commencement of the Kṛta-yuga.

युगादितिथि
yugādi-tithi  (EI 13), see yug-ādi.

युगादिपर्वन्
Yugādi-parvan  (EI 14), name of an auspicious time;<BR>same as yugādi-tithi.

युगल
yugala  (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.

युगन्धरी
yugandharī  (EI 11), same as javār (jawār), millet.

युग्म
yugma  (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.

युग्यचर्य
Yugyacarya  (CII 1), a charioteer.

युज्
yuj  (CII 1), cf. vṛddhir=yujyatām, ‘should devote themselves for an increase’;<BR>śāśvataṁ samayam=[etad]=yuñjyuḥ, ‘they may strive for this at all times’. Cf. yoga.

